{"id": 36, "ts": 1778845833.9431376, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "I have reviewed the information we all hold on the four candidates and identified the remaining gaps that could affect our final decision.\n**What we still do not know**\n- **Candidate\u202fA:** No explicit statement about reliability (e.g., \u201cknown to be reliable\u201d) or any documented teamwork/communication strengths beyond \u201cvery good leadership qualities.\u201d\n- **Candidate\u202fD:** No explicit reliability rating or track record; also no positive evidence of teamwork or crew\u2011integration beyond \u201ctakes responsibility seriously.\u201d\n**What we do know**\n- **Candidate\u202fB** is the only candidate with a clear \u201c100\u202f% reliable\u201d rating, proven calmness in crises, solid weather\u2011assessment ability, and strong computer/avionics skills. The interpersonal drawbacks (pretentiousness, occasional wrong tone, nasty remarks) are serious but appear potentially addressable through CRM training.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** shows quick, correct decision\u2011making, a crew\u2011centric attitude (\u201cputs concern for others above everything\u201d), excellent attention skills, conscientiousness, and technical understanding, but suffers from communication difficulty, egocentric behavior, and a lack of willingness to pursue further education.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** offers proactive safety (anticipates dangerous situations), strong situational awareness (sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision), and leadership qualities, yet is described as unfriendly, unhealthy, and unorganized, with no explicit reliability evidence.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** demonstrates solid problem\u2011solving, concentration, and a serious sense of responsibility, but is described as moody, a loner, and again lacks any explicit reliability statement.\n**Targeted questions to fill the gaps**\n1. **Agent\u202f1 or Agent\u202f2:** Do you have any